descript.abstract: This map layer portrays Presidential general election results for 2012, with results reported by county or county equivalent, for the 50 United States and the District of Columbia.
descript.purpose: These data are intended for geographic display and analysis at the national level, and for large regional areas. The data should be displayed and analyzed at scales appropriate for 1:1,000,000-scale data. No responsibility is assumed by the National Atlas of the United States in the use of these data.

procstep.procdesc: The county boundaries file was used as a starting point. Because Alaska reports results by State legislative district, county boundaries for Alaska were deleted and Alaska legislative district boundaries were added to the file. Kalawao County and Maui County, HI were merged into a single area. The State election results data sets were downloaded and joined to the boundaries file using the FIPS attribute. The Missouri Secretary of State reported Jackson County and Kansas City voting totals separately; the votes for both entities were combined into Jackson County. In New York, both Mitt Romney and Barack Obama appeared on the ballot under more than one party; votes were totaled based on the candidate, not the political party. Oklahoma only reported votes for the Republican and Democratic parties; votes were assigned to the appropriate candidate. Rhode Island and Massachusetts report results by towns and cities. City and town results were aggregated into the county in which the city or town is located. The vote total for cities and towns in Rhode Island does not match the State total, because overseas military and civilians residing overseas are issued ballots that contain only federal offices; these votes are therefore not assigned to a particular city or town and are not included in this data set. Kalawao County and Maui County, Hawaii results are reported together.
